//@version=6
// ============================================================================
// Market State Engine [WavesUnchained]
// Version: 2.0.0
// Author: WavesUnchained
// Build: 2026-07-15 10:26:01
// ============================================================================
// Context engine that classifies market state, value location, structural
// bias, and energy phase — instead of generating a standalone buy/sell signal.
//
// Features:
//   ✓ Orthogonal Structure Regime, Energy Phase, and Auction Location axes
//   ✓ Score-arbitrated nine-state classifier with dominance-based Transition
//   ✓ Adaptive value zone (VWMA/EMA/Hybrid) with Discount/Value/Premium location
//   ✓ Auction Pressure from close-position, failed auctions, absorption, and value-extreme reaction
//   ✓ Direction-aware compression/expansion/exhaustion energy scoring
//   ✓ Bar-close state machine with confirmation bars, minimum dwell, and emergency opposite-state override
//   ✓ Selectable structure smoothing (EMA/DEMA/KAMA/JMA Approx), with JMA Approx as default
//   ✓ Net-progress impulse memory and reaction-confirmed pullback readiness
//   ✓ Confirmed higher-timeframe structural context (advisory by default, optional strict gate)
//   ✓ Balance/compression zones with interruption grace, width limits, state history, and acceptance-based breakouts
//   ✓ Shock-bar guard pauses rather than immediately deleting a valid raw zone
//   ✓ Zone quality encoded via border thickness (running average State Quality), fill/border by pressure
//   ✓ Box profile with ATR width, edge reactions, failed breaks, volume, anchored VWAP, and breakout quality
//   ✓ State, zone, and breakout hover labels with contextual metrics
//   ✓ Four-level Long/Short context and reaction-based readiness markers
//   ✓ Optional context dashboard and bar-close state-change/zone-breakout alerts
//
// ============================================================================
indicator(
     "Market State Engine [WavesUnchained]",
     shorttitle = "MSE",
     overlay = true,
     max_boxes_count = 100,
     max_labels_count = 300,
     max_lines_count = 100
)
